    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=433\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"616\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544640874\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544640862\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"69e5c5c9-4c05-401e-8178-bb2277121639\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1800&amp;height=866 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=433 1x\"></span><p>Artists and Studios can harness the creative flexibility of MaterialX and RenderMan, creating a variety of materials from glass, metals, SSS, plastics, and common PBR workflows using the <em>mtlxStandard</em> node inside of Solaris</p><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_Network.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=391\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_Network.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"557\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544640880\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_Network.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544640862\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"4dbf86b1-218c-4e76-9897-90d372a093cd\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_Network.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1800&amp;height=782 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_Network.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=391 1x\"></span><p>Working with MaterialX shading nodes works in the same way as you would with other RenderMan materials.  Simply create your MaterialX shading network in a <em>materialLibrary</em> and assign it to geo as usual.<br/><br/><br/></p><hr/><h2 id=\"Solaris&amp;MaterialX-Limitations\">Limitations</h2><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_chessSet.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=432\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_chessSet.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"615\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544640877\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_chessSet.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544640862\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"44266f1f-e2d2-4c85-b2d7-08f899fea257\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_chessSet.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1800&amp;height=864 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544640862/RenderMan_MaterialX_Solaris_chessSet.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433081851&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=432 1x\"></span><p>For the moment, there are a number of limitations with rendering MaterialX in Solaris with RenderMan, which include </p><ul><li><p>MaterialX Subnets are not currently supported.</p></li><li><p>Rendering with XPU is currently not supported.</p></li></ul><p /><p><br/><br/><br/></p>"
    }
